// =============================================================================
// ecosystem/clay_ui_synthetics.rs — Clay UI single-header library stubs
//
// Clay is a single-header C UI library whose internal array types are
// generated by the macro:
//
//     CLAY__ARRAY_DEFINE(TYPE, NAME)
//
// which expands to NAME ## Array, NAME ## Array_Add, NAME ## Array_Get,
// NAME ## Array_Set, NAME ## Array_Allocate_Arena, etc. Tree-sitter parses
// the raw macro invocations but cannot expand them, so the fully-qualified
// function names never appear as symbols in the index, leaving every call
// site as an unresolved ref.
//
// Clay also defines several CLAY_* enum constant families (alignment,
// attach-point, text-wrap, etc.) whose definitions live inside
// `#if defined(CLAY_IMPLEMENTATION)` blocks that are conditionally compiled
// but unconditionally referenced.
//
// This module synthesises:
//   * Every CLAY__ARRAY_DEFINE instantiation used by cpp-clay (the
//     concrete type/name pairs observed in the unresolved-refs table).
//   * The CLAY_* enum constants that appear as unresolved refs.
//   * Public types like Clay_RectangleElementConfig that the extractor
//     misses due to typedef-inside-macro patterns.
//
// Activation: a `clay.h` file is present in the project root (the
// canonical distribution shape for this single-header library). The
// locate_roots implementation returns an empty vec when clay.h is absent,
// which prevents the ecosystem from firing on unrelated C projects.
// =============================================================================

